<i>How my love slighted me</i>

564
00:51:12,460 --> 00:51:14,622
I thought we were
rather good together.

565
00:51:14,700 --> 00:51:15,986
So did I.

566
00:51:16,140 --> 00:51:18,984
We would make a fine duo.

567
00:51:19,140 --> 00:51:21,029
I wanted to thank you
for not approaching me

568
00:51:21,140 --> 00:51:22,983
on that subject again.

569
00:51:24,820 --> 00:51:27,300
Well, it has not been easy.

570
00:51:35,820 --> 00:51:37,822
Do you wish me to, er,

571
00:51:37,900 --> 00:51:39,664
accompany you back to the house?

572
00:51:40,820 --> 00:51:42,743
No, I like to walk around
the farm every night

573
00:51:42,820 --> 00:51:44,549
to make sure all is safe.

574
00:51:45,740 --> 00:51:49,028
Then I...
I can walk with you.

575
00:51:49,380 --> 00:51:51,382
I've done it many times alone.

576
00:51:52,500 --> 00:51:54,025
Good night,
Mr. Boldwood.

577
00:51:54,100 --> 00:51:56,785
You've been very kind.
A pleasure to see you.

578
00:52:32,220 --> 00:52:33,790
Who are you?

579
00:52:33,980 --> 00:52:35,584
I'm sorry.
I seem to be lost.

580
00:52:36,100 --> 00:52:38,785
We're entangled.
Are you hurt?

581
00:52:39,100 --> 00:52:40,226
No.

582
00:52:40,380 --> 00:52:41,460
I'm looking for Weatherbury.

583
00:52:41,540 --> 00:52:42,701
I hope I didn't startle you.

584
00:52:42,780 --> 00:52:44,908
We've got hitched
together somehow.

585
00:52:44,980 --> 00:52:46,470
Here, allow me.

586
00:52:46,580 --> 00:52:49,060
No. No. Please,
let me do it myself.

587
00:52:50,820 --> 00:52:53,266
If you lift your
foot for a moment.

588
00:53:07,460 --> 00:53:08,950
Please don't stare.

589
00:53:09,100 --> 00:53:11,785
I don't think I've ever seen
a face as beautiful as yours.

590
00:53:16,260 --> 00:53:20,106
You shouldn't be here.
Please let me have the lamp.

591
00:53:30,540 --> 00:53:33,669
A mighty impressive
harvest this looks like.

592
00:53:45,380 --> 00:53:46,461
Miss,

593
00:53:47,380 --> 00:53:48,825
look.

594
00:53:52,780 --> 00:53:54,305
Who is he, Liddy?

595
00:53:54,460 --> 00:53:56,622
Sergeant Francis Troy.

596
00:53:56,700 --> 00:53:59,863
Noble blood, full of promise.
Very sharp and trim.

597
00:54:01,140 --> 00:54:02,140
Well-educated.

598
00:54:02,180 --> 00:54:03,989
There was good things
expected of him.

599
00:54:04,460 --> 00:54:07,145
He threw it all in
to be a soldier.

600
00:54:08,740 --> 00:54:10,185
Well, I won't have it.

601
00:54:10,340 --> 00:54:11,865
What are you doing, miss?

602
00:54:11,980 --> 00:54:14,187
I'm going to tell him to leave.

603
00:54:19,300 --> 00:54:20,631
Sergeant Troy,

604
00:54:20,700 --> 00:54:23,226
I must absolutely insist that
you leave at this very moment.

605
00:54:23,340 --> 00:54:24,830
I can't.

606
00:54:24,980 --> 00:54:26,823
Will you follow me, please?

607
00:54:47,420 --> 00:54:49,024
What angers you, exactly?

608
00:54:50,180 --> 00:54:51,180
Please.

609
00:54:51,220 --> 00:54:53,188
What I said
or the way I said it?

610
00:54:53,340 --> 00:54:54,910
You must know.

611
00:54:55,380 --> 00:54:56,506
There must be some man

612
00:54:56,580 --> 00:54:57,980
who tells you
that you're beautiful.

613
00:54:58,180 --> 00:55:00,148
Oh, not to my face, not...

614
00:55:00,220 --> 00:55:01,984
But there is someone
who kisses you?

615
00:55:02,060 --> 00:55:03,221
I've never been kissed.

616
00:55:09,900 --> 00:55:13,109
Why couldn't you have just
passed by and said nothing?

617
00:55:14,620 --> 00:55:15,781
Do you forgive me?

618
00:55:18,220 --> 00:55:19,870
I do not.
Why?

619
00:55:20,060 --> 00:55:22,506
Because the things you say...

620
00:55:22,580 --> 00:55:24,469
I said that you were beautiful.

621
00:55:29,380 --> 00:55:31,747
I wonder if you fight
as well as you speak.

622
00:55:31,820 --> 00:55:33,106
Better.

623
00:55:38,820 --> 00:55:42,302
Meet me. Tomorrow.

624
00:55:43,740 --> 00:55:45,469
I can't.

625
00:55:45,620 --> 00:55:46,826
You don't want to?

626
00:55:46,980 --> 00:55:48,266
Yes, but...

627
00:55:48,340 --> 00:55:49,751
Then you must.
I mustn't.

628
00:55:50,060 --> 00:55:51,789
Nobody would know.

629
00:55:54,500 --> 00:55:56,184
Please go now.

630
00:55:57,100 --> 00:55:58,431
Tomorrow.

631
00:55:59,100 --> 00:56:00,431
8:00.

632
00:56:01,620 --> 00:56:03,622
The hollow in the ferns.

633
00:58:03,860 --> 00:58:04,861
Do you trust me?

634
00:58:06,540 --> 00:58:07,621
I do.

635
00:58:13,620 --> 00:58:15,384
I give you my word as a soldier,

636
00:58:15,460 --> 00:58:17,269
I will not harm you.

637
00:58:17,380 --> 00:58:19,382
The sword is blunt,

638
00:58:19,900 --> 00:58:22,744
but you must not flinch.

639
00:58:23,300 --> 00:58:25,382
I'll try not to.

640
00:59:11,100 --> 00:59:12,989
You cut my hair.

641
00:59:15,700 --> 00:59:17,623
This sword could skin you alive.

642
00:59:18,140 --> 00:59:20,620
But you told me I was safe.

643
00:59:20,780 --> 00:59:23,226
And you were.
Entirely safe.

644
00:59:23,820 --> 00:59:25,948
I gave you my word.

645
00:59:27,660 --> 00:59:29,788
Now I will take this.

646
01:00:47,740 --> 01:00:49,265
Miss Everdene.

647
01:00:50,700 --> 01:00:52,464
Perhaps I could walk with you?

648
01:00:52,580 --> 01:00:55,106
I'm quite happy
to walk by myself.

649
01:00:57,060 --> 01:00:59,427
You should have nothing
to do with him.

650
01:00:59,780 --> 01:01:01,782
He's not good enough for you.

651
01:01:02,260 --> 01:01:04,388
He's a perfectly decent man.

652
01:01:05,620 --> 01:01:06,906
That's not what I believe.

653
01:01:06,980 --> 01:01:09,586
Why? What have you heard?

654
01:01:10,940 --> 01:01:14,422
You don't know him at all.
It's all rumors.

655
01:01:14,820 --> 01:01:16,380
Prejudice simply because
he's a soldier.

656
01:01:16,420 --> 01:01:18,900
I like soldiers.
But not this one.

657
01:01:18,980 --> 01:01:21,426
I believe him to have
no conscience at all.

658
01:01:22,460 --> 01:01:24,827
Stay clear.
Don't listen to him.

659
01:01:24,900 --> 01:01:26,584
Don't believe him.

660
01:01:26,940 --> 01:01:28,271
Get rid of him.

661
01:01:28,660 --> 01:01:30,469
And what is it to you?

662
01:01:33,580 --> 01:01:35,184
I'm not such a fool
as to imagine

663
01:01:35,260 --> 01:01:38,230
I might stand a chance now
that you are so above me.

664
01:01:38,300 --> 01:01:42,146
But don't suppose I'm content
to stay a nobody all my life.

665
01:01:42,620 --> 01:01:45,271
One day I will leave you.
You can be sure of that.

666
01:01:45,820 --> 01:01:47,948
But for now,
I care for you too much

667
01:01:48,020 --> 01:01:50,341
to see you go to ruin
because of him.

668
01:01:52,300 --> 01:01:55,144
So if you don't mind, I'll...

669
01:01:57,100 --> 01:01:59,262
I'll stay by your side.

670
01:02:01,460 --> 01:02:03,462
Good evening.

671
01:02:21,300 --> 01:02:23,382
<i>Mr. Boldwood,</i>

672
01:02:23,460 --> 01:02:26,430
<i>you have been a dear friend
to me these past months.</i>

673
01:02:26,500 --> 01:02:28,787
<i>And it is because
I value our friendship</i>

674
01:02:28,860 --> 01:02:31,306
<i>so greatly that I am writing.</i>

675
01:02:32,020 --> 01:02:35,024
<i>I am honored by your proposal</i>

676
01:02:35,140 --> 01:02:37,302
<i>and have given it much thought,</i>

677
01:02:37,420 --> 01:02:39,787
<i>but I must tell you that,
to my own surprise,</i>

678
01:02:39,860 --> 01:02:42,067
<i>I have undergone
what can only be described</i>

679
01:02:42,140 --> 01:02:44,507
<i>as a change of heart</i>

680
01:02:44,580 --> 01:02:47,345
<i>and I'm afraid
I cannot accept your offer.</i>

681
01:03:10,540 --> 01:03:13,066
I wasn't sure you'd be here.

682
01:03:13,380 --> 01:03:15,587
Where else would I be?

683
01:03:18,020 --> 01:03:19,704
You ready?

684
01:03:22,180 --> 01:03:24,023
Are you sure?

685
01:03:28,380 --> 01:03:30,542
How does this sound?

686
01:03:31,620 --> 01:03:34,385
Mrs. Bathsheba Troy.

687
01:03:50,100 --> 01:03:51,431
All right?

688
01:04:47,780 --> 01:04:49,464
Walk on.

689
01:06:37,180 --> 01:06:40,263
Gentlemen.
Ladies and gentlemen.

690
01:06:41,940 --> 01:06:46,309
A short time ago,
I had the privilege

691
01:06:47,260 --> 01:06:52,187
and the simple fortune
of meeting this angel.

692
01:06:53,060 --> 01:06:54,550
Your mistress.

693
01:06:55,380 --> 01:06:58,543
And now I stand before
you her husband,

694
01:06:59,580 --> 01:07:00,911
your master,

695
01:07:02,140 --> 01:07:04,825
and the proudest man
you will ever see.

696
01:07:05,300 --> 01:07:09,385
So, please, charge your glasses

697
01:07:09,460 --> 01:07:14,387
and sing out to
my most beautiful wife,

698
01:07:15,020 --> 01:07:18,741
Mrs. Bathsheba Troy.

699
01:07:24,620 --> 01:07:27,829
Miss Everdene,
there's going to be a storm.

700
01:07:27,940 --> 01:07:31,740
Oak, you big lump.
To me.

701
01:07:31,820 --> 01:07:33,743
There's going to be a storm.

702
01:07:33,820 --> 01:07:36,983
We need to protect the ricks
or we'll lose the harvest.

703
01:07:37,660 --> 01:07:39,981
I need five to six men
for an hour, no more.

704
01:07:40,100 --> 01:07:41,784
Frank, perhaps we ought to...
No.

705
01:07:41,860 --> 01:07:43,510
Darling, it's our
wedding celebration.

706
01:07:44,660 --> 01:07:48,984
It will not rain tonight.
My wife forbids it.

707
01:07:49,660 --> 01:07:51,628
Now if you'll excuse me.

708
01:07:52,620 --> 01:07:54,463
Friends!

709
01:07:55,340 --> 01:07:56,341
One more thing.

710
01:07:57,740 --> 01:08:02,302
I may no longer
be Sergeant Troy,

711
01:08:02,420 --> 01:08:06,391
But I remain a soldier
in this one respect!

712
01:08:07,660 --> 01:08:11,301
The finest bottles
of French brandy,

713
01:08:12,300 --> 01:08:15,509
a triple-strength dose
for every man.

714
01:08:15,620 --> 01:08:16,781
Cheers! To your health!

715
01:08:57,500 --> 01:09:02,347
<i>"Pretty Polly, Pretty Polly
It's I've come a-wooin"'</i>

716
01:09:02,900 --> 01:09:08,066
<i>"Pretty Polly, Pretty Polly
It's I've come a-wooin"'</i>

717
01:09:09,380 --> 01:09:12,065
<i>She says, "Creep and crawl
through the window, then</i>

718
01:09:12,260 --> 01:09:14,024
<i>"And let's get doin'</i>

719
01:09:14,100 --> 01:09:18,628
<i>"And lay your leg over me
Over me, do</i>

720
01:09:19,300 --> 01:09:24,300
<i>"Oh, me britches is tight
and I cannot undo 'em</i>

721
01:09:29,940 --> 01:09:32,147
<i>"There's a knife
on the windowsill</i>

722
01:09:32,220 --> 01:09:33,745
<i>"Love, take it to 'em</i>

723
01:09:34,300 --> 01:09:36,951
<i>"And lay your leg over me..."</i>

724
01:09:56,300 --> 01:10:01,022
<i>About 40 weeks after,
the fine baby come bawlin'</i>

725
01:10:02,140 --> 01:10:06,589
<i>Never regretted
that creepin' and crawlin'</i>

726
01:10:06,700 --> 01:10:09,829
<i>"Lay your leg over me
Over me..."</i>

727
01:10:57,780 --> 01:10:59,145
Gabriel!

728
01:11:01,820 --> 01:11:02,821
Gabriel!

729
01:11:05,060 --> 01:11:06,266
What can I do?

730
01:11:06,380 --> 01:11:08,269
It's too dangerous!

731
01:11:08,340 --> 01:11:09,865
I'm coming up!

732
01:11:20,140 --> 01:11:21,266
Hold it down.

733
01:11:22,500 --> 01:11:24,389
Still no rain.

734
01:11:24,820 --> 01:11:26,504
It'll come.

735
01:11:40,300 --> 01:11:44,464
Come on, hold me!
Come here. Come here.

736
01:11:50,100 --> 01:11:52,228
Come here. Come on.

737
01:12:12,900 --> 01:12:14,982
Gabriel, I've been a fool.

738
01:12:15,660 --> 01:12:19,142
I've always had contempt
for silly girls

739
01:12:19,260 --> 01:12:22,582
dazzled by flattery
in a scarlet uniform and...

740
01:12:22,900 --> 01:12:25,790
And now I've done
what I swore I would never do.

741
01:12:28,020 --> 01:12:30,466
But he told me
about another woman,

742
01:12:31,260 --> 01:12:33,627
a woman more beautiful
that he'd loved before,

743
01:12:33,700 --> 01:12:35,589
and I couldn't bear it.

744
01:12:37,500 --> 01:12:39,343
So somewhere between
jealousy and distraction,

745
01:12:39,420 --> 01:12:40,546
I married him.

746
01:12:41,100 --> 01:12:43,990
I don't want an opinion
on the subject, I just...

747
01:12:44,500 --> 01:12:46,423
In fact, I forbid it.

748
01:12:51,860 --> 01:12:53,191
Go to bed.

749
01:12:54,420 --> 01:12:56,821
I'll finish it on my own.

750
01:12:57,820 --> 01:12:59,504
Gabriel...

751
01:13:03,060 --> 01:13:04,710
Thank you.

752
01:13:29,860 --> 01:13:30,986
Sir?

753
01:13:35,300 --> 01:13:36,506
Mr. Boldwood, sir!

754
01:13:37,380 --> 01:13:40,429
I wanted to ensure your
mistress' crops were safe.

755
01:13:40,780 --> 01:13:43,545
Good work, Gabriel.
She's lucky to have you.

756
01:13:44,780 --> 01:13:46,509
Wait a moment, sir.

757
01:13:54,580 --> 01:13:55,866
You seem unwell, sir.

758
01:13:56,740 --> 01:13:58,344
You should go home.

759
01:14:00,260 --> 01:14:01,261
Yes.

760
01:14:04,220 --> 01:14:06,188
Yes, I will.

761
01:14:11,460 --> 01:14:12,825
Oak.

762
01:14:14,820 --> 01:14:18,029
You know that things have
not gone well with me, lately.

763
01:14:19,620 --> 01:14:23,625
I was going to get a little
settled in life. But, er...

764
01:14:27,660 --> 01:14:29,662
It was not to be.

765
01:14:32,620 --> 01:14:34,907
I daresay I'm something of a...

766
01:14:35,740 --> 01:14:37,902
A joke about the parish.

767
01:14:38,780 --> 01:14:42,307
But I do wanna make
one thing clear.

768
01:14:42,820 --> 01:14:45,824
There was no jilting
on her part.

769
01:14:46,860 --> 01:14:51,548
We were never engaged.
No matter what people say.

770
01:14:53,220 --> 01:14:55,063
She promised me nothing.

771
01:15:00,700 --> 01:15:02,589
And yet,

772
01:15:03,180 --> 01:15:04,670
Gabriel,

773
01:15:07,780 --> 01:15:11,466
I feel the most terrible grief.

774
01:15:18,060 --> 01:15:20,222
Not a word to her.

775
01:15:21,340 --> 01:15:23,911
We understand each other, yes?

776
01:15:26,060 --> 01:15:27,061
Yes, sir.

777
01:16:19,220 --> 01:16:20,267
Damn and bother!

778
01:16:23,700 --> 01:16:25,190
Sit.

779
01:16:25,420 --> 01:16:27,741
Stay. Now, turn around.

780
01:16:33,900 --> 01:16:35,106
Can you spare a coin, please?

781
01:16:35,260 --> 01:16:36,500
No, no.

782
01:16:40,620 --> 01:16:41,951
Hit him!

783
01:16:42,500 --> 01:16:43,501
Come on!

784
01:16:44,980 --> 01:16:46,584
Knock him out!

785
01:16:47,900 --> 01:16:49,504
Hit him!

786
01:16:54,220 --> 01:16:56,587
Pay up.
Pay up, Mr. Troy.

787
01:16:57,420 --> 01:16:59,104
Just take it.

788
01:17:04,820 --> 01:17:05,901
Sir, excuse me.

789
01:17:05,980 --> 01:17:07,630
Could you spare a coin, please?

790
01:17:08,100 --> 01:17:09,545
No.

791
01:17:12,100 --> 01:17:13,261
Fanny?

792
01:17:21,140 --> 01:17:22,471
Hello, Frank.

793
01:17:24,780 --> 01:17:26,145
Hello.

794
01:17:28,540 --> 01:17:29,826
You're so pale.

795
01:17:30,500 --> 01:17:31,786
Oh, Frank.

796
01:17:31,860 --> 01:17:34,022
Darling, your hands are shaking.

797
01:17:34,540 --> 01:17:37,510
I thought you said
All Souls, not All Saints.

798
01:17:37,580 --> 01:17:39,582
I went to the wrong church.

799
01:17:40,700 --> 01:17:44,705
When I got there, you'd gone.
And I don't blame you,

800
01:17:44,780 --> 01:17:47,181
but it's been very hard,
Frank. I...

801
01:17:47,260 --> 01:17:48,591
Not now.

802
01:17:49,780 --> 01:17:52,067
My wife mustn't see you.

803
01:17:52,700 --> 01:17:54,111
Your wife?

804
01:18:04,860 --> 01:18:07,227
Mrs. Troy is very beautiful.

805
01:18:08,940 --> 01:18:10,624
No more than you.

806
01:18:13,260 --> 01:18:17,743
Frank, I must tell you,
I'm carrying your child.

807
01:18:17,980 --> 01:18:19,345
What?

808
01:18:31,620 --> 01:18:34,703
What if I told you that
I'd made a terrible mistake,

809
01:18:36,220 --> 01:18:38,507
but that I will make amends?

810
01:18:39,540 --> 01:18:40,871
I swear on my life

811
01:18:40,940 --> 01:18:43,830
I will find a home
for you and our baby.

812
01:18:44,260 --> 01:18:46,103
You've sworn before, Frank.

813
01:18:46,300 --> 01:18:48,143
No, this time... This time...

814
01:18:55,740 --> 01:18:58,391
Go to Budmouth.
Stay at the Union.

815
01:18:58,460 --> 01:19:00,349
The workhouse, Frank?

816
01:19:00,420 --> 01:19:02,263
Tonight, just tonight.
One night.

817
01:19:02,340 --> 01:19:05,184
And then meet me tomorrow
at 10:00 on the bridge.

818
01:19:05,620 --> 01:19:07,702
I'll bring you
all the money I have

819
01:19:07,780 --> 01:19:09,191
and I'll find a home for you.

820
01:19:09,460 --> 01:19:11,349
You'll be safe, my darling.

821
01:19:11,420 --> 01:19:14,867
And I promise you, I promise you

822
01:19:14,980 --> 01:19:17,028
I will make amends.

823
01:19:22,340 --> 01:19:24,024
Get back in the carriage.

824
01:19:24,380 --> 01:19:26,269
Do you know who that woman is?

825
01:19:26,580 --> 01:19:27,741
I do.

826
01:19:27,980 --> 01:19:29,186
Who is she?

827
01:19:29,340 --> 01:19:30,466
She's nothing.

828
01:19:31,660 --> 01:19:33,708
Get back in the carriage.

829
01:19:34,660 --> 01:19:36,025
Frank...

830
01:20:45,220 --> 01:20:47,871
Could you let me have £20?

831
01:20:50,460 --> 01:20:51,950
What for?

832
01:20:52,660 --> 01:20:54,230
I need it.

833
01:20:56,420 --> 01:20:59,344
If you continue to gamble,
we will lose the farm.

834
01:20:59,460 --> 01:21:00,541
It's not for gambling.

835
01:21:00,700 --> 01:21:01,781
What's it for?

836
01:21:01,940 --> 01:21:03,021
Why should it matter
what it's for?

837
01:21:03,100 --> 01:21:04,431
It's my money.

838
01:21:04,900 --> 01:21:07,028
I work for it, don't I?

839
01:21:07,100 --> 01:21:09,671
No. You don't.

840
01:21:10,420 --> 01:21:12,582
Not proper farm work.

841
01:21:14,460 --> 01:21:16,906
Don't do something
you'll regret.

842
01:21:19,180 --> 01:21:22,821
The money is required
for farm expenses.

843
01:22:09,740 --> 01:22:11,344
No mistake, Mr. Oak.

844
01:22:11,420 --> 01:22:14,071
This was Miss Robbin's
last known abode.

845
01:22:14,140 --> 01:22:15,346
Fanny was
my uncle's servant

846
01:22:15,420 --> 01:22:17,149
and we shall treat
her with respect.

847
01:22:18,060 --> 01:22:20,188
Perhaps we should
take her to the church,

848
01:22:20,260 --> 01:22:21,750
just for tonight.

849
01:22:21,820 --> 01:22:24,187
No, bring her inside, please.

850
01:22:44,740 --> 01:22:46,504
What did she die of, Liddy?

851
01:22:48,220 --> 01:22:49,949
I don't know, miss.

852
01:22:52,140 --> 01:22:53,824
There were rumors, but...

853
01:22:54,660 --> 01:22:57,311
Fanny had a sweetheart,
didn't she?

854
01:22:57,780 --> 01:22:59,384
Yes, miss.

855
01:23:00,700 --> 01:23:02,623
A soldier.

856
01:23:06,620 --> 01:23:09,464
Please, come
and sit upstairs with me.

857
01:23:26,580 --> 01:23:29,743
I seem to cry
a great deal these days.

858
01:23:32,340 --> 01:23:33,865
I never used to cry at all.

859
01:23:44,460 --> 01:23:45,461
Good night, Liddy.

860
01:23:46,500 --> 01:23:48,389
'Night, miss.

861
01:24:44,340 --> 01:24:45,785
What?

862
01:24:46,340 --> 01:24:47,466
Who is it?

863
01:24:47,580 --> 01:24:48,991
I can't say...

864
01:24:49,140 --> 01:24:50,630
Stay, stay. Stay.

865
01:25:10,620 --> 01:25:12,622
Don't kiss them, Frank.

866
01:25:12,980 --> 01:25:15,381
I'm still your wife.

867
01:25:23,060 --> 01:25:25,870
This woman, dead as she is,

868
01:25:25,940 --> 01:25:31,868
is more to me than you
ever were, or are, or can be.

869
01:25:34,340 --> 01:25:36,468
You are nothing to me now.

870
01:25:38,860 --> 01:25:40,669
Nothing.

871
01:27:48,260 --> 01:27:50,262
Mrs. Troy?

872
01:27:53,740 --> 01:27:55,788
I'm afraid...

873
01:27:55,860 --> 01:27:58,306
I'm afraid your
husband has drowned.

874
01:29:32,300 --> 01:29:33,381
That's a great
responsibility, sir.

875
01:29:33,460 --> 01:29:34,461
Nonsense.

876
01:29:34,540 --> 01:29:35,905
No reason why a man
of your ability

877
01:29:35,980 --> 01:29:38,506
shouldn't be able to
superintend two farms.

878
01:29:38,660 --> 01:29:39,866
And why shouldn't there
be stronger links

879
01:29:39,940 --> 01:29:41,590
between our establishments?

880
01:29:41,660 --> 01:29:45,346
Think of it. Two thousand
acres under your sole charge.

881
01:29:45,580 --> 01:29:47,469
A share of my profits.

882
01:29:47,580 --> 01:29:48,661
Miss Everdene needs me here.

883
01:29:48,740 --> 01:29:50,151
And her farm will have priority.

884
01:29:50,220 --> 01:29:51,631
I'd still need
Miss Everdene's permission.

885
01:29:51,700 --> 01:29:52,781
But, of course.

886
01:29:52,860 --> 01:29:54,021
Of course, I wouldn't
dare do anything

887
01:29:54,100 --> 01:29:55,829
without her blessing. And,

888
01:29:55,940 --> 01:29:58,511
if it'll help
sway your decision,

889
01:30:02,740 --> 01:30:05,266
there's an old comrade
of yours here.

890
01:30:07,220 --> 01:30:08,221
Georgie!

891
01:30:08,380 --> 01:30:09,541
Had to go all the way
to Norcombe Hill

892
01:30:09,620 --> 01:30:10,667
to find this old fella.

893
01:30:10,940 --> 01:30:12,021
You pleased?

894
01:30:12,380 --> 01:30:14,064
Yes, sir, very much.

895
01:30:14,180 --> 01:30:17,024
And I'll have your
decision soon, yes?

896
01:30:17,460 --> 01:30:18,985
You will, sir.

897
01:30:19,220 --> 01:30:21,029
Hey, Georgie.

898
01:30:23,100 --> 01:30:24,101
Come on. Come on.

899
01:30:35,460 --> 01:30:36,905
Come on! Come on!

900
01:30:38,740 --> 01:30:41,220
Gabriel, you're
getting on in the world.

901
01:30:41,780 --> 01:30:43,908
Of course you must
accept the offer.

902
01:30:44,020 --> 01:30:46,148
Only with
your approval.

903
01:30:46,460 --> 01:30:48,269
If I lose the farm,
there may be no future

904
01:30:48,340 --> 01:30:50,388
for any of us here.

905
01:30:50,860 --> 01:30:53,067
You know where my loyalty lies.

906
01:30:55,580 --> 01:30:57,662
You're a man of great talent.

907
01:30:57,980 --> 01:30:59,311
It's only natural
that you should rise.

908
01:30:59,380 --> 01:31:01,621
I've no desire to hold you back.

909
01:31:12,700 --> 01:31:13,826
Thank you.

910
01:31:19,220 --> 01:31:21,302
Come on, Georgie.
Come on.

911
01:31:25,380 --> 01:31:30,591
Forgive me.
I understand there are debts.

912
01:31:32,020 --> 01:31:33,624
Your late husband.

913
01:31:34,820 --> 01:31:37,505
Perhaps... Perhaps we should
change the subject.

914
01:31:37,580 --> 01:31:39,264
Perhaps I can help.

915
01:31:43,740 --> 01:31:46,550
Mr. Boldwood,
that's a very kind offer,

916
01:31:46,620 --> 01:31:49,146
but I would never dream
of accepting any money.

917
01:31:53,540 --> 01:31:55,781
I am a middle-aged man

918
01:31:57,340 --> 01:32:00,628
willing to protect you
for the rest of your life.

919
01:32:02,940 --> 01:32:06,786
You may run your farm,
if you wish. Without risk.

920
01:32:09,060 --> 01:32:10,630
I'll pay your

921
01:32:11,700 --> 01:32:13,782
departed husband's debts

922
01:32:13,900 --> 01:32:16,062
and guarantee
its financial stability.

923
01:32:17,420 --> 01:32:19,627
It can be your pastime.

924
01:32:21,900 --> 01:32:24,585
Of course, we'd need to wait,

925
01:32:25,060 --> 01:32:27,108
for propriety's sake.

926
01:32:27,820 --> 01:32:29,584
But when you're ready,

927
01:32:30,380 --> 01:32:32,508
I'm offering you shelter.

928
01:32:33,540 --> 01:32:37,545
Comfort. A safe harbor.

929
01:32:40,620 --> 01:32:42,384
As my wife.

930
01:32:46,900 --> 01:32:49,187
You must at least admire
my persistence.

931
01:32:52,380 --> 01:32:53,586
I do.

932
01:32:53,660 --> 01:32:54,661
And like me?

933
01:32:54,740 --> 01:32:55,821
Yes.

934
01:32:57,020 --> 01:32:59,421
And respect me?

935
01:32:59,500 --> 01:33:01,468
Yes. Very much.

936
01:33:01,540 --> 01:33:03,861
Which is it?
Like or respect?

937
01:33:07,420 --> 01:33:10,549
It is difficult for a woman
to define her feelings

938
01:33:10,620 --> 01:33:13,226
in a language chiefly
made by men to express theirs.

939
01:33:13,340 --> 01:33:16,184
If you worry about a lack
of passion on your part,

940
01:33:16,260 --> 01:33:17,864
a lack of, er,

941
01:33:20,500 --> 01:33:21,990
desire,

942
01:33:22,940 --> 01:33:25,546
if you worry about marrying me

943
01:33:25,620 --> 01:33:28,544
merely out of guilt,

944
01:33:28,860 --> 01:33:30,464
and, er,

945
01:33:31,460 --> 01:33:35,624
pity and compromise, well...

946
01:33:36,900 --> 01:33:38,504
I don't mind.

947
01:33:42,740 --> 01:33:44,469
When must you
give your answer?

948
01:33:44,580 --> 01:33:46,184
By Christmas.

949
01:33:48,020 --> 01:33:49,863
It's a terrible responsibility.

950
01:33:52,500 --> 01:33:54,946
I hold that man's
future in my hands.

951
01:33:55,580 --> 01:33:57,708
His sanity, too, perhaps.

952
01:33:57,780 --> 01:33:59,066
Could you care for him?

953
01:33:59,140 --> 01:34:01,507
You may suppose
love is wanting.

954
01:34:03,380 --> 01:34:06,429
But love's a worn-out,
miserable thing for me now.

955
01:34:06,500 --> 01:34:08,548
Why are you
asking me?

956
01:34:12,980 --> 01:34:15,586
I need someone who's objective.

957
01:34:15,660 --> 01:34:17,264
Indifferent.

958
01:34:18,740 --> 01:34:21,550
Then I'm afraid you're
asking the wrong man.

959
01:34:39,900 --> 01:34:41,504
Good evening, Mr. Oak.

960
01:34:43,180 --> 01:34:44,670
Good evening.

961
01:35:03,060 --> 01:35:04,141
That's it.

962
01:35:04,300 --> 01:35:05,347
Mind.

963
01:35:15,620 --> 01:35:21,104
<i>Rejoice</i>

964
01:35:21,180 --> 01:35:25,185
<i>Emmanuel</i>

965
01:35:25,300 --> 01:35:28,065
<i>Shall come to thee</i>

966
01:35:28,180 --> 01:35:33,107
<i>O Israel</i>

967
01:35:36,220 --> 01:35:40,225
<i>O come, Thou Rod of Jesse...</i>

968
01:35:40,980 --> 01:35:43,347
I appreciate you
coming along, Oak.

969
01:35:43,420 --> 01:35:44,421
Ah!

970
01:35:44,580 --> 01:35:46,901
Yes, very good.
Well done. Erm...

971
01:35:46,980 --> 01:35:48,027
Just more... More things.

972
01:35:48,180 --> 01:35:49,181
Yes, sir.

973
01:35:53,420 --> 01:35:56,583
So what do you think?

974
01:35:57,180 --> 01:35:59,865
I'm not in the habit of
organizing parties.

975
01:36:00,100 --> 01:36:02,580
Perhaps we should make it
an annual event.

976
01:36:02,660 --> 01:36:03,786
Every Christmas Eve.

977
01:36:04,340 --> 01:36:05,865
I've invited the whole village.

978
01:36:05,940 --> 01:36:07,021
Do you think they'll come?

979
01:36:07,100 --> 01:36:09,102
Do you think
Miss Everdene will come?

980
01:36:09,220 --> 01:36:10,745
I'm sure she will.

981
01:36:12,020 --> 01:36:13,021
Yes.

982
01:36:13,780 --> 01:36:15,782
And you'll come too, I hope.

983
01:36:16,900 --> 01:36:19,506
I know Miss Everdene
would like you to be here.

984
01:36:19,580 --> 01:36:21,025
Perhaps, for an hour or so.

985
01:36:26,020 --> 01:36:29,502
Look, I'm shaking.
I'm so nervous.

986
01:36:30,500 --> 01:36:32,662
Gabriel, will you...

987
01:36:33,020 --> 01:36:34,306
As well as you can, please.

988
01:36:34,460 --> 01:36:35,825
I'll try.

989
01:36:35,900 --> 01:36:38,904
Is there a knot that's
particularly fashionable?

990
01:36:40,900 --> 01:36:43,028
You're asking the wrong man.

991
01:36:44,620 --> 01:36:46,031
What about women?

992
01:36:46,940 --> 01:36:49,102
Does a woman keep her promise?

993
01:36:50,380 --> 01:36:51,984
She has promised?

994
01:36:52,740 --> 01:36:54,742
An implied promise.

995
01:36:56,620 --> 01:36:58,031
Once again, I'm...

996
01:36:58,180 --> 01:36:59,545
Will she do what's right?

997
01:37:02,220 --> 01:37:04,143
If it's not inconvenient to her.

998
01:37:05,180 --> 01:37:07,467
Oak, you've become
quite cynical lately.

999
01:37:08,460 --> 01:37:10,224
She never promised
that first time.

1000
01:37:10,300 --> 01:37:13,702
Therefore, she has
never broken her promise.

1001
01:37:14,180 --> 01:37:16,501
She hasn't promised
this time, either.

1002
01:37:17,460 --> 01:37:20,828
But she will. Tonight.

1003
01:37:21,300 --> 01:37:22,825
I know she will.

1004
01:37:24,780 --> 01:37:26,270
And when she does...

1005
01:37:32,100 --> 01:37:35,866
I wanted to tell you
in advance, Gabriel,

1006
01:37:37,420 --> 01:37:40,424
because I... I believe
I know your secret.

1007
01:37:43,580 --> 01:37:46,186
I've seen you together.

1008
01:37:47,620 --> 01:37:49,702
The way you speak to her.

1009
01:37:50,860 --> 01:37:52,430
And watch her.

1010
01:37:54,020 --> 01:37:56,148
And look after her.

1011
01:37:56,460 --> 01:37:58,781
And I know her, er,

1012
01:38:00,220 --> 01:38:03,747
profound affection for you.

1013
01:38:04,300 --> 01:38:06,587
You've behaved like a man,

1014
01:38:07,420 --> 01:38:08,831
and as the successful rival,

1015
01:38:08,900 --> 01:38:11,983
successful through
your kindness,

1016
01:38:12,060 --> 01:38:13,061
I wish to tell you

1017
01:38:15,540 --> 01:38:17,861
I am profoundly grateful.

1018
01:38:22,300 --> 01:38:24,871
The cook would like a word, sir.

1019
01:39:33,100 --> 01:39:35,068
Kiss me. Joseph.

1020
01:39:35,140 --> 01:39:37,142
No, please don't.
Liddy, don't.

1021
01:40:00,700 --> 01:40:02,429
Would you excuse me?

1022
01:40:08,300 --> 01:40:10,109
I've come to say good night.

1023
01:40:10,220 --> 01:40:12,427
Go back and talk to
the poor things.

1024
01:40:12,500 --> 01:40:14,582
You've broken their hearts.

1025
01:40:15,180 --> 01:40:17,501
I don't suit
this kind of affair.

1026
01:40:18,540 --> 01:40:20,781
No. Nor do I.

1027
01:40:21,780 --> 01:40:23,908
I wish I could go, too.

1028
01:40:33,540 --> 01:40:34,746
I must go.

1029
01:40:34,860 --> 01:40:37,750
Not before you've danced.
Both of you.

1030
01:40:37,860 --> 01:40:39,225
I insist.

1031
01:40:42,820 --> 01:40:44,470
Mr. Oak?

1032
01:40:46,940 --> 01:40:48,430
Thank you.

1033
01:41:16,980 --> 01:41:18,982
Tell me what to do.

1034
01:41:23,860 --> 01:41:25,305
Gabriel?

1035
01:41:32,580 --> 01:41:34,423
Do what is right.

1036
01:41:38,300 --> 01:41:40,109
Sorry, excuse me.

1037
01:42:25,500 --> 01:42:26,945
Frank.

1038
01:42:28,420 --> 01:42:30,548
Black suits you.

1039
01:42:32,300 --> 01:42:34,462
Although a little premature.

1040
01:42:39,700 --> 01:42:41,543
You're alive.

1041
01:42:42,140 --> 01:42:45,826
And here I am.
Pulled from the sea.

1042
01:42:46,100 --> 01:42:49,422
Some fishermen found me
and brought me to shore.

1043
01:42:50,260 --> 01:42:52,661
Then I discovered I was dead
and found I preferred it.

1044
01:42:54,860 --> 01:42:56,510
For a while, anyway.

1045
01:42:56,780 --> 01:42:58,384
Why have you come back?

1046
01:42:58,540 --> 01:43:00,110
The strangest thing.

1047
01:43:01,340 --> 01:43:03,069
I missed you.

1048
01:43:04,740 --> 01:43:07,220
You don't seem very
happy to see me.

1049
01:43:07,500 --> 01:43:09,901
You said I was nothing to you.

1050
01:43:10,220 --> 01:43:11,585
Did I?

1051
01:43:13,340 --> 01:43:17,789
Well, then.
Honesty at all times.

1052
01:43:18,540 --> 01:43:21,464
I find myself in need of money.

1053
01:43:22,420 --> 01:43:23,831
I gave up my profession for you,

1054
01:43:23,900 --> 01:43:25,664
and it seems a little harsh

1055
01:43:25,820 --> 01:43:27,060
that you have a farm and a house

1056
01:43:27,100 --> 01:43:29,182
while I'm living off nothing.

1057
01:43:29,340 --> 01:43:30,751
There is no money.

1058
01:43:30,900 --> 01:43:32,311
Then sell the farm.

1059
01:43:44,140 --> 01:43:45,505
Come home.

1060
01:43:50,300 --> 01:43:51,745
No.

1061
01:43:53,860 --> 01:43:57,148
I said, come home.

1062
01:43:59,180 --> 01:44:01,786
I'm your husband
and you'll obey me!

1063
01:44:18,620 --> 01:44:20,031
Oh, my God.

1064
01:45:49,500 --> 01:45:51,150
Let me see.

1065
01:45:53,900 --> 01:45:54,981
If it's
any consolation,

1066
01:45:55,060 --> 01:45:56,903
his life will be spared.

1067
01:45:58,700 --> 01:46:00,429
Crime of passion.

1068
01:46:27,420 --> 01:46:28,945
Morning, Liddy.

1069
01:46:31,300 --> 01:46:33,029
It's a
fine harvest, ma'am.

1070
01:46:33,100 --> 01:46:34,590
Best we've had in years.

1071
01:46:34,700 --> 01:46:36,260
Will we have it all over
before the dew?

1072
01:46:36,300 --> 01:46:39,702
We will indeed, ma'am.
Luck's been on our side.

1073
01:46:45,540 --> 01:46:48,749
Come, Liddy, give me a hand.

1074
01:47:14,260 --> 01:47:16,422
I'm sorry I startled you.

1075
01:47:18,060 --> 01:47:19,585
I wanted to tidy up for them.

1076
01:47:19,660 --> 01:47:21,788
I haven't been here for so long.

1077
01:47:24,900 --> 01:47:26,504
Are you going in?

1078
01:47:27,020 --> 01:47:30,183
Rehearsals.
I sing bass in the choir.

1079
01:47:30,460 --> 01:47:32,303
Yes, I've heard you.

1080
01:47:32,660 --> 01:47:35,425
Then I apologize.

1081
01:47:39,140 --> 01:47:41,984
I've been hoping to get
a chance to talk to you.

1082
01:47:42,780 --> 01:47:46,546
We've... We've not spoken
as much as I'd have liked.

1083
01:47:47,700 --> 01:47:49,031
No.

1084
01:47:57,700 --> 01:47:59,941
I'm leaving England.

1085
01:48:03,860 --> 01:48:05,385
Leaving?

1086
01:48:06,660 --> 01:48:08,662
Going to America.

1087
01:48:09,620 --> 01:48:12,146
There's a boat leaving
Bristol in four days' time.

1088
01:48:12,220 --> 01:48:13,710
I'll be on it.

1089
01:48:14,180 --> 01:48:15,864
Now that the farm is secure.

1090
01:48:17,060 --> 01:48:19,904
I understand I should
give you notice.

1091
01:48:22,060 --> 01:48:25,223
No. You must go
when you want.

1092
01:48:29,900 --> 01:48:32,141
I'll leave first thing tomorrow.

1093
01:48:32,220 --> 01:48:33,710
No fuss.

1094
01:48:35,540 --> 01:48:36,871
I think that's best.

1095
01:50:24,140 --> 01:50:25,187
Gabriel!

1096
01:50:30,660 --> 01:50:31,991
Gabriel.

1097
01:50:32,860 --> 01:50:34,271
Wait.

1098
01:50:51,940 --> 01:50:53,988
You'll think I'm strange, but...

1099
01:50:55,500 --> 01:50:57,787
I've been worried.
Have I offended you somehow?

1100
01:50:57,900 --> 01:50:59,470
No, not at all.

1101
01:51:00,700 --> 01:51:02,304
Is it money?

1102
01:51:03,220 --> 01:51:04,904
I'll pay you whatever you want.

1103
01:51:05,020 --> 01:51:06,829
I don't need money now.

1104
01:51:07,860 --> 01:51:09,350
A formal partnership, then?

1105
01:51:09,500 --> 01:51:11,025
Nor a partnership.

1106
01:51:12,020 --> 01:51:14,227
The farm belongs to you alone.

1107
01:51:14,340 --> 01:51:16,661
It's the finest farm
for miles around.

1108
01:51:16,740 --> 01:51:18,822
Then why else are you leaving?

1109
01:51:18,900 --> 01:51:20,823
I said I'd leave you one day.

1110
01:51:24,860 --> 01:51:27,261
Well, you must not go.

1111
01:51:28,180 --> 01:51:29,420
You forbid me?

1112
01:51:29,580 --> 01:51:30,866
Yes, if you like.

1113
01:51:31,580 --> 01:51:33,105
I forbid you.

1114
01:51:35,500 --> 01:51:38,424
It's time for you
to fight your own battles.

1115
01:51:39,260 --> 01:51:41,024
And win them, too.

1116
01:51:44,100 --> 01:51:46,068
So we should
say good-bye, then?

1117
01:51:47,500 --> 01:51:49,264
I suppose so.

1118
01:51:59,940 --> 01:52:01,271
Gabriel, wait.

1119
01:52:06,060 --> 01:52:07,789
Thank you, Gabriel.

1120
01:52:09,540 --> 01:52:11,907
You've believed in me
and fought for me

1121
01:52:12,900 --> 01:52:13,900
and stood by my side when

1122
01:52:13,940 --> 01:52:16,591
all the rest of the world
is against me.

1123
01:52:18,540 --> 01:52:20,986
And we've been through
so much together.

1124
01:52:25,620 --> 01:52:27,748
Wasn't I your first sweetheart?

1125
01:52:30,420 --> 01:52:32,149
Weren't you mine?

1126
01:52:38,380 --> 01:52:41,145
And now I'd have to
go on without you.

1127
01:52:45,620 --> 01:52:47,622
If I knew...

1128
01:52:52,660 --> 01:52:54,105
If I knew that you would

1129
01:52:54,180 --> 01:52:56,911
let me love you and marry you...

1130
01:52:57,020 --> 01:52:58,784
But you will never know.

1131
01:53:00,780 --> 01:53:02,270
Why not?

1132
01:53:03,460 --> 01:53:05,827
Because you never ask!

1133
01:53:06,500 --> 01:53:08,343
Would you say no again?

1134
01:53:10,300 --> 01:53:11,631
I don't know.

1135
01:53:13,460 --> 01:53:15,030
Probably.

1136
01:53:21,940 --> 01:53:23,783
So why don't you?

1137
01:53:25,540 --> 01:53:27,190
Ask me.

1138
01:53:31,300 --> 01:53:32,950
Ask me.

1139
01:53:37,540 --> 01:53:38,951
Ask me, Gabriel.

1140
01:56:26,540 --> 01:56:32,229
<i>Come all you fair
and tender girls</i>

1141
01:56:32,300 --> 01:56:38,148
<i>That flourish in your prime</i>

1142
01:56:38,220 --> 01:56:44,148
<i>Beware, beware
Keep your garden fair</i>

1143
01:56:44,220 --> 01:56:49,220
<i>Let no man steal your thyme</i>

1144
01:56:57,540 --> 01:57:03,183
<i>For when your thyme
it is past and gone</i>

1145
01:57:03,260 --> 01:57:09,347
<i>He'll care no more for you</i>

1146
01:57:09,420 --> 01:57:11,661
<i>And every place</i>

1147
01:57:11,740 --> 01:57:15,426
<i>Where your thyme was waste</i>

1148
01:57:15,540 --> 01:57:20,540
<i>Will all spread o'er with rue</i>

1149
01:57:27,740 --> 01:57:33,349
<i>The gardener's son
was standing by</i>

1150
01:57:33,460 --> 01:57:39,183
<i>Three flowers he gave to me</i>

1151
01:57:39,300 --> 01:57:45,148
<i>The pink, the blue
and the violet true</i>

1152
01:57:45,220 --> 01:57:50,220
<i>And the red, red rosy tree</i>

1153
01:57:57,460 --> 01:58:02,466
<i>But I refused the red rose bush</i>

1154
01:58:03,420 --> 01:58:08,631
<i>And gained the willow tree</i>

1155
01:58:09,420 --> 01:58:14,460
<i>That all the world
may plainly see</i>

1156
01:58:15,300 --> 01:58:20,943
<i>How my love slighted me</i>

1157
01:58:22,940 --> 01:58:28,504
<i>How my love slighted me</i>
